cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.AR, cs.EM 

This paper focuses on improving the reliability and range of backscatter communications for IoT devices, which involves signal processing, wireless networking, and hardware design. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the fundamental limits and practical algorithms for reliable communication over noisy channels. The paper also discusses the system-level challenges and trade-offs in implementing backscatter systems, which could fall into cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper proposes a new encoding scheme and hardware design for backscatter tags, which could be relevant to cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) and cs.EM (Embedded Systems).
